Ms Word Basic:
    1. Create New Files :- [Ctrl + N]
    2. Open File [ctrl + O]
    3.Save a file [ctrl + s]
    4. close a file [Alt + F4]
    5. Navigate in a file
    6. Word interface


Formating text :
    1. Font
    2. Font Style
        Bold [ctrl + b]
        italic [ctrl + i]
        Underline


    3. Font Color
    4. Font Size    = Ctrl + Shift + F

    5. Text Highlighter Color
    6. Clear Formats
    7. Change Case

Editing text :
    1. cut [ctrl + x]
    2.copy [ctrl + c]
    3.paste [ctrl + v]
    4.undo [ctrl + z]
         select line and put color and reverse back.
    5.Redo [ctrl + y]
        same work reverse i.e color lines.
    6.Find [ctrl + F]
        Find some word in ms file.
    7.Replace [ctrl + H]
        Replace some word with new word i.e online Replace with offline

   =rand(2,2)
   shift and right arrow key
   ctrl + Shift and right arrow key (select one word at a time)

